25/05/2008
VATICAN CITY, Vatican -- Pope Benedict XVI received a Bulgarian delegation led by Foreign Minister Ivaylo Kalfin Friday (May 23rd). 
The audience occurred on May 24th -- the Day of Slav Letters, Bulgarian Education and Culture. 
Pope Benedict XVI blessed Bulgaria. 
He appealed to Christians to emulate the unity evident in the shared tradition of Cyril and Methodius, fathers of the Cyrillic alphabet. 
Kalfin and the pontiff also discussed some issues related to Vatican properties in Sofia. 
(bTV, BNR, BTA, New.bg - 24/05/08)
